  "special_rules": [
    {
      "name": "Imperial Void Shields",
      "text": "Imperial Titans are protected by void shield generators. The number of void shields each Titan has is noted on its datasheet. Each void shield automatically stops one point of damage and then goes down. Do not make saves for damage stopped by void shields and do not allocate blast markers. Once all shields are down, the Titan may be damaged normally. Close combat hits ignore void shields, but firefight hits must first knock down shields. Void shields can be repaired. Each Titan can repair one downed void shield in the end phase of each turn. If a Titan regroups, it can use the dice roll to either repair shields or remove blast markers."
    }
  ],
